
Some commonly used vim-go commands:

- :GoDef / :GoDefPop — go to definition / come back    mapped to Ctrl-] and Ctrl-p


bar:
	$(MAKE) -C foo bar
bar:
	$(MAKE) -C foo bar
- :GoInfo — show type info for identifier under cursor
- :GoReferrers — find all references
- :GoImplements — show interfaces implemented
- :GoBuild / :GoRun / :GoTest — build/run/test
- :GoRename — rename identifier
- :GoFmt — format (runs automatically on save by default)
- :GoImports — add/remove imports
- :GoLint / :GoVet / :GoMetaLinter
- :GoDoc — show documentation
- :GoCallers / :GoCallees — call graph
- :GoFillStruct — fill struct literal with zero values
- :GoAddTags / :GoRemoveTags — struct field tags

Full list with :help go-commands.  (May need to first run :helptags ALL)


The default mappings (all buffer-local to Go files):

  Definition navigation (g:go_def_mapping_enabled, on by default):
  - Ctrl-] → :GoDef
  - Ctrl-t → :GoDefPop
  - gd → :GoDef

  Documentation (g:go_doc_keywordprg, on by default):
  - K → :GoDoc

  Text objects (g:go_textobj_enabled, on by default):
  - if / af — inner/around function body
  - ic / ac — inner/around comment block

verify with :help go-mappings, and :verbose map
